The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 London, Dec. 23 (PTI): An Indian doctor working in the National Health Service in London has been asked to retrain after deficiencies were found in his treatment of five young patients.           
	The General Medical Council found a string of charges against Dr Ravi Manikonda true after a 20-day disciplinary hearing in Manchester. The consultant paediatrician now needs to retrain and abide by a list of 13 conditions for 18 months. He had failed to diagnose a painful bowel condition.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Editors Guild of India has formed an ethics committee to check the increasing number of reports of paid news in media organisations.                   
	 Kochi (PTI): The wife of PDP leader Abdul Nasser Madani, Soofiya Madani, was granted conditional bail in Kochi on Wednesday in a Tamil Nadu bus burning case. The bail was given on a bond of Rs 1 lakh and two sureties of the same amount. She has been asked to surrender her passport and appear before investigating officers within a week.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): A 17-year-old boy allegedly jumped to death from the balcony of his house, apparently depressed over the performance in his exams. Abhishek Venkats parents said he had been depressed for the past 15 days and had not given two of his papers.                  
	 Ahmedabad (PTI): The 17th National Children Science Congress, aimed at cultivating scientific temperament among young students, will be held here from December 27 to 31. The theme for the five-day event will be conservation and exploration of the Earth. Over 600 students, aged between 10 and 17 from across the country, will participate.                  
	 Madurai (PTI): A woman has been arrested in Madurai for allegedly peddling drugs. Police found 21kg of ganja on her. Two of her accomplices fled during check by a patrol team.
                                                                                                                                              
